    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-16T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="689"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/959: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-16T20:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 16, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 16—10:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>845. Unusual political activity has been observable in Tokyo during the last
                    several days. Among many other conferences it is reported that Prince Kanin,
                    Chief of the Army General Staff, Prince Fushimi, Chief of the Naval General
                    Staff, and Matsuoka, Minister for Foreign Affairs, have twice called on the
                    Emperor during the past week, all three officials having been last received on
                    September 14. This morning an extraordinary meeting of the entire Cabinet is
                    reported as having taken place at the Premier’s residence to discuss “an
                    important state affair”.</p>
                <p>This activity is generally believed to be connected with Japan’s policy of
                    southward advance<note n="42" xml:id="d689fn42">See <ref
                            target="frus1940v04#pg_1">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 1</ref>
                        ff.</note> but it is impossible to confirm this supposition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
